1/* $NetBSD: notify.h,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:30 riastradh Exp $ */

3#ifndef __NVKM_NOTIFY_H__
4#define __NVKM_NOTIFY_H__
5#include <core/os.h>
6struct nvkm_object;
7
8struct nvkm_notify {
9 struct nvkm_event *event;
10 struct list_head head;
11#define NVKM_NOTIFY_USER 0
12#define NVKM_NOTIFY_WORK 1
13 unsigned long flags;
14 int block;
15#define NVKM_NOTIFY_DROP 0
16#define NVKM_NOTIFY_KEEP 1
17 int (*func)(struct nvkm_notify *);
18
19 /* set by nvkm_event ctor */
20 u32 types;
21 int index;
22 u32 size;
23
24 struct work_struct work;
25 /* this is const for a *very* good reason - the data might be on the
26 * stack from an irq handler. if you're not core/notify.c then you
27 * should probably think twice before casting it away...
28 */
29 const void *data;
30};
31
32int nvkm_notify_init(struct nvkm_object *, struct nvkm_event *,
33 int (*func)(struct nvkm_notify *), bool work,
34 void *data, u32 size, u32 reply,
35 struct nvkm_notify *);
36void nvkm_notify_fini(struct nvkm_notify *);
37void nvkm_notify_get(struct nvkm_notify *);
38void nvkm_notify_put(struct nvkm_notify *);
39void nvkm_notify_send(struct nvkm_notify *, void *data, u32 size);
40#endif
